The 'period from filing to granting' is calculated as the difference between the current date and the filing date, converted to days.

sql:
SELECT patent_id, COUNT(keyword_id) AS number_of_keywords
FROM patent_keywords
GROUP BY patent_id;

external_knowledge:
A patent is considered granted when it is officially approved and awarded by the relevant patent office; 
The maintenance fee is a recurring payment required to keep the patent in force;
A valid grant date refers to a date when the patent was officially granted, not a projected or anticipated date.

sql:
SELECT patent_id, fee_amount
FROM patent_maintenance_fees
WHERE fee_amount = (
    SELECT MAX(fee_amount) FROM patent_maintenance_fees
);
